claim.claim-text:
A method for preparing a bone graft composition, the method comprising steps of:
(1) preparing a bone morphogenetic protein solution by mixing a solvent and a bone morphogenetic protein;
(2) adsorbing the bone morphogenetic protein onto graft material powder by mixing the bone morphogenetic protein and the graft material powder;
(3) mixing and stirring the graft material powder having the bone morphogenetic protein adsorbed thereon and hydroxypropyl methylcellulose powder to obtain a mixture, and forming a gel from the mixture such that a dissolution rate of the hydroxypropyl methylcellulose powder reaches 50% or more within 48 hours; and
(4) forming a structure containing a plurality of pores by freeze-drying the gel under vacuum.
